<br>
A note to add about not using snare - it doesnt actually save you mana in the long run due to a few reasons:<br>
<br>
- You have to run further (to get the range for cast time), means fights last that bit longer.<br>
- If you get a fizzle then thats mana/more time running off again<br>
- Although snare costs what, 75 mana or something, even doing this twice (resist - usually only need one), you will still have the same amount of mana as if you hadnt snared (since fight will be over quicker, and you will be medding)<br>
<br>
Even if the last wasnt true - without using snare, your likely to get hit one or two times, which means new shield needs to go up, with snaring i only need to re-apply shield after 4 or 5 quads, unles something went wrong during pull.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
